The much-awaited Sh 250 million Green Park Bus Terminal will commence operations in phases starting on Tuesday, Nairobi Metropolitan Services has announced. In a public notice issued on Monday, NMS announced that PSVs plying Ngong' road and Argwings Kodhek road will pick and drop passengers at the Green Park Bus Terminal from Tuesday, May 24, 2022 “Nairobi Metropolitan Services wishes to inform Public Service Vehicle (PSVs) operators and the general public that the Green Park Bus Terminal will commence operations in phases,” reads the notice Matatus plying Lang'ata road will start operations at the terminus three days later on May 27, 2022. Green Park is among six other termini the NMS is setting up following President Uhuru Kenyatta’s directive back in March 2020. The others include Desai, Park Road, Ladhies-Muthurwa, Fig Tree terminus and Bunyala-Workshop Road. The terminal located opposite Kenya Railways club has a capacity to accommodate 300 to 350 vehicles at any given time and up to 20,000 matatus in a day.